Different approach that requires less code looks as follows:
```
@Slf4j
@RequiredArgsConstructor
final class XmlFieldBodyFilter implements BodyFilter {

    private static final Predicate&lt;String&gt; XML = MediaTypeQuery.compile(&quot;*/xml&quot;, &quot;*/*+xml&quot;);

    private final Collection&lt;String&gt; parameters;
    private final String replacement;

    @Override
    public String filter(@Nullable final String contentType, final String body) {
        return XML.test(contentType) &amp;&amp; StringUtils.isNotBlank(body) ? censorBody(body) : body;
    }

    private String censorBody(final String body) {
        return parameters.stream().reduce(body, this::censorBody);
    }

    private String censorBody(String text, String parameterToReplace) {
        var pattern = compile(&quot;(&lt;%s&gt;)(.*)(&lt;/%s&gt;)&quot;.formatted(parameterToReplace, parameterToReplace));
        var matcher = pattern.matcher(text);
        var result = new StringBuilder(text.length());

        while (matcher.find()) {
            if (matcher.groupCount() == 3) {
                matcher.appendReplacement(result, String.join(&quot;&quot;, matcher.group(1), replacement, matcher.group(3)));
            }
        }
        matcher.appendTail(result);

        return result.toString();
    }

}

//Instance creation
new XmlFieldBodyFilter(List.of(&quot;Password&quot;), &quot;XXX&quot;);
```
It&#39;s based on regex. And solved issues I had with requirement to set `http://apache.org/xml/features/disallow-doctype-decl` to false.

